reviewText: Like the three movies,this is good family entertainment.It's a one-hour concert of songs from the original,nicely staged and well-performed by a spirited young cast.The dance numbers are sensational,and the behind-the-scenes stuff is fun.Very entertaining.High School Musical: The ConcertHigh School Musical (Encore Edition)High School Musical 2 (Extended Edition)High School Musical 3: Senior Year

reviewText: Teenagers will probably love this movie, but as a grown up Man, I did notlike this film at all.  Reminded me of when I went to see in concert Cindi Lauper (sp?) it the girlthat sings "Girls just want to have fun"  And it was full of little girls and teenagers that justloved her.  I enjoyed that concert very much, in fact she had me in the isles dancing as weremany kids.  This film is just about little teenage people singing songs i.e. in concert.I turned it off after listening to 15 minutes of it.  Where they were introducing the characters.And each one of just started singing and introducing themselves.
summary: As an Adult - I hate this movie!
Title: High School Musical: The Concert Extreme Access Pass

Title: High School Musical: The Concert Extreme Access Pass

reviewText: This is footage of a touring concert staring many of the cast from the film.  The lead male "Zac" is absent however and this was the first thing my little ones noticed.  The singing still entertains and the performance does include some new songs that the artists are promoting from their new solo albums.  If you have the film you could do without this version as it is a repetition of the same tunes.  If you are a fan you will enjoy seeing the stars sing the old favourites all over again.
Title: High School Musical: The Concert Extreme Access Pass
